Chess

Members: James Hua, Leon Loi, James Yang

Summary
    Play chess between two different computers thorugh using command-line arguments
    Players will type out commands in order to move the piece to a particular square
    on the board.


TECHNICAL DESIGN

    Board
        Dynamic array to manipulate pieces
        Working with files for starting board
        
    Playing the game
        Parsing arguments typed through Terminal
        Use of shared memory and semaphores to limit number of people
        Networking
        
        
        
REACH GOALS

    Human vs AI
        Play against a computer
        

TIMELINE

    1/08: Basic board implemented
    1/13: Parsing command-line arguments
    1/17: Shared memory / Semaphore implementation
    1/21: Networking
    1/23: Debugging
